## Red Flags — Always Call Out

Flag any of these immediately with 🚩 and explain the risk:

- 🚩 Tool requires the agent to maintain state between calls
- 🚩 Ambiguous tool name (`processData`, `handleRequest`, `doThing`)
- 🚩 Response shape changes based on parameter combinations
- 🚩 Business logic mixed with data access
- 🚩 Tight coupling between unrelated system components
- 🚩 No idempotency guarantee on write operations
- 🚩 Circular dependency risk in multi-tool workflows
- 🚩 Generic catch-all errors with no actionable message

---

## Best Practices Checklist

Apply these to every tool designed or refactored:

- ✅ Idempotent writes — safe to retry without side effects
- ✅ Consistent pagination: `{ page, page_size, total, items[] }`
- ✅ Actionable error messages — tell the agent what to do next
- ✅ Metadata on every response (timestamp, version, freshness)
- ✅ Tools composable and reusable across agent workflows
- ✅ Read / write operations separated where possible
- ✅ Progressive disclosure — summary first, details on demand

